snippet.title: THE BENGAL FILES Official Trailer | Vivek Agnihotri | Abhishek A | Pallavi J | Zee Studios | 5 Sept
snippet.description:
From the makers of The Kashmir Files and The Tashkent Files, here is the official trailer of THE BENGAL FILES, the powerful conclusion to the trilogy by two-time National Award-winning filmmaker Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri.

A presentation by: Tej Narayan & Snehlatha Agarwal and I Am Buddha

Directed by: Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri
Produced by: Abhishek Agarwal, Pallavi Joshi and Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri 
Worldwide Release: Zee Studios
Music: Zee Music Co.
Starring: Mithun Chakraborty, Anupam Kher, Pallavi Joshi, Darshan Kumaar, Simratt Kaur

This September, witness the untold truth of the Hindu genocide.

#TheBengalFiles #RightToLife

snippet.description:
The Great Shinobi War  | Academy Trials Day 3 #freefire #gyangaming #freefirelive 

Schedule
Date : 14 AUG 2025
IDP Time : 08:00 PM 
START Time : 08:10 PM

Participating Teams :

KIRIGAKURE

ASSASSIN ARMY
AURA ESPORTS 
BLACK FLAG ARMY 
TOTAL GAMING 
ASIN ARMY
MPG
MR JAY
VOLTER GAMING
RFF ESPORTS 
JD MAX
AAWARI GAMER 
GWM ARMY




Team Distribution & Grouping

48 Total Teams:

- 24 from Partner Program
- 12 from Extended Program
- 12 from Open Qualifiers

4 Groups of 12 Teams each:

- Konohagakure (Hidden Leaf Village)
- Sunagakure (Hidden Sand Village)
- Kirigakure (Hidden Mist Village)
- Kumogakure (Hidden Cloud Village)

Tournament Format & Roadmap


Stages & Details:

Academy Trials

- 4 Groups (12 teams each)
- 6 matches per group
- Top 6 teams from each group qualify


Ninja Vanguard

- 2 Groups (12 teams each)
- 6 matches per group
- Top 6 teams from each group qualify


Great Shinobi War (Grand Finals)

- 12 Final teams
- 12 matches in a 1-day grand final
- Winner crowned champion


Shinobi Reckoning (Clash Squad Showdown)

- Top 8 teams from Grand Finals
- Quarterfinals: Best of 1 matches
- Semifinals: Best of 3 matches
- Finals: Best of 5 matches

Tournament Timeline

- Day 1 (14 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Konohagakure (Hidden Leaf Village)
- Day 2 (15 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Sunagakure (Hidden Sand Village)
- Day 3 (16 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Kirigakure (Hidden Mist Village)
- Day 4 (17 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Kumogakure (Hidden Cloud Village)
- Day 5 (18 August): Ninja Vanguard ‚Äì Group A
- Day 6 (19 August): Ninja Vanguard ‚Äì Group B
- Day 7 (20 August): Great Shinobi War ‚Äì Grand Finals
- Day 8 (21 August): Shinobi Reckoning ‚Äì Clash Squad Showdown

Prize Pool Distribution

Total Prize Pool: 3,00,000 Diamonds

- Champion: 1,20,000 Diamonds
- Runner-Up: 50,000 Diamonds
- Second Runner-Up: 30,000 Diamonds
- Most Valuable Player (MVP): 20,000 Diamonds
- Clash Squad Winner: 80,000 Diamonds

‚ú® Achyutam Keshavam ‚Äì A Devotional Krishna Bhajan ‚ú®
 "Achyutam Keshavam" is a timeless and soul-soothing bhajan dedicated to Lord Krishna, praising their divine names, virtues, and forms. The bhajan beautifully recites various names of the Lord - Achyuta, Keshava, Narayana, and more - each carrying deep spiritual meaning.
Singing this bhajan is believed to purify the heart, remove sorrows, and bring the blessings of the Supreme Lord. It reminds devotees to surrender completely to God, trusting His eternal protection and grace.


üå∏ Chant ‚ÄúAchyutam Keshavam‚Äù with devotion and invite divine bliss into your life.

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.
